---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';

const lastUpdated = '09/03/2026';
const pageUrl = 'https://cryptocalk.com/privacy/';
const webPageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  url: pageUrl,
  description:
    'Read CryptoCalk privacy policy: what data is and is not collected, how client-side storage is used, and third-party data provider details.',
  inLanguage: 'en',
};
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Read CryptoCalk privacy policy: what data is and is not collected, how client-side storage is used, and third-party data provider details."
  lang="en"
>
  <SiteHeader lang="en" currentPath="/privacy" />
  <main id="main-content" class="policy-page">
    <article class="policy-card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        CryptoCalk is a calculator-first website. Most computations are performed directly in your browser. We are committed to minimising data collection and explaining clearly what is stored on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We do not require account registration and we do not ask for personal identity data to use calculators.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>No signup forms and no profile creation.</li>
        <li>No wallet connection required for basic calculator usage.</li>
        <li>No KYC data collection through CryptoCalk calculators.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Browser Storage</h2>
      <p>
        To improve performance and user experience, CryptoCalk uses limited browser storage:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>`localStorage`: theme preference (`light` or `dark`).</li>
        <li>`sessionStorage`: short-lived cached market data from CoinGecko API responses.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can clear this data at any time from your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Data Providers</h2>
      <p>
        Some calculators use live market prices sourced from CoinGecko API. Requests are made from your browser to their endpoints. Please review CoinGecko's policy for their own data handling terms.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies, Analytics and Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        CryptoCalk uses Google Analytics (gtag.js) to understand how visitors use the site. Google Analytics collects standard internet log information and visitor behaviour patterns anonymously. This information is only processed in a way that does not identify anyone.
      </p>
      <p>
        We display advertisements through <strong>Google AdSense</strong>. Google and its partners may use cookies (including the DoubleClick cookie) to serve ads based on your prior visits to this site or other sites. You can opt out of personalised advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a> or by visiting <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aboutads.info</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior visits to CryptoCalk. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to our site and/or other sites on the internet. Users may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting Google's <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Advertising Policy</a>.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Advertising Policies</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.coingecko.com/en/privacy" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">CoinGecko Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        Because most operations are client-side, retained data is primarily what your browser stores locally. Server-level logs may exist for operational security and uptime management, and are handled under standard hosting retention windows.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        CryptoCalk is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child, please contact us immediately.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Financial Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        CryptoCalk provides educational tools and scenario calculators. Nothing on this site is financial, legal, or tax advice.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including the right to access, correct, or delete data held about you. Since CryptoCalk does not maintain user accounts or personal databases, most calculator data exists only in your browser's local storage. You can clear it at any time from your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects when it was last revised. We encourage you to review this page periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, data requests, or concerns about this policy, please contact us directly:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@cryptocalk.com">support@cryptocalk.com</a></li>
        <li>Contact form: <a href="/contact/">cryptocalk.com/contact/</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter lang="en" />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(webPageSchema)} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    padding: 48px 20px 72px;
  }

  .policy-card {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    padding: 34px 28px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 2.8vw, 2.2rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .meta {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 8px 0 12px 20px;
    padding: 0;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
</style>
